               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470510-name-1128" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1128" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1128" type="surname" value="M'GUIRE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1128" type="given" value="MATTHEW"></interp>MATTHEW M'GUIRE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Greenwich pensioner. I met the prisoner on Saturday, the 1st of May—I went to a public-house and had a pot of the ale with him—I put half-a-crown on the table—the boy brought the ale and took up the half-crown—the prisoner got up and met the boy before he came back, and asked him for the change—he said the half-crown was his own—it was not his, it was mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you put it down on the table or did I? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I took it out of my pocket and put it down—I swear it was mine—you did not put it on the table.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470510-name-1129" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1129" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1129" type="surname" value="BATCHELOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1129" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD BATCHELOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Philip Langford, who keeps the public-house. I took the half-crown from the table and went for the change—the prisoner came out and asked me for the change of his half-crown—I did not know whose it was—I gave him the two shillings.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did I put the half-crown towards you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—it was lying on the table—I did not know whose it was.</p>
